;################################################### DESCRIPTION
@Node "1_Description" "Well, spank my arse!"
  @{fg shine}@{u}                                                                        @{uu}@{fg text}

                         @{b}»·D·E·S·C·R·I·P·T·I·O·N·>@{ub}
  @{u}                                                                        @{uu}

  Y'know, how come programs with loads of features look crap?

  A  program  will  either  look  good and be crap, or be look crap and be
  good.   On  my  ever  eternal  quest,  I'm going to try and rectify this
  situation.

  @{i}Trinity  Player@{ui}  is  a  program  that (hopefully) looks great, and works
  great  too!   Obviously  everyones'  tastes  differ,  so that's why I've
  included  the  GUI  graphics  for you, so you can design your own if you
  want to - send any ones you do to @{"me" link "5_Author"}!

  Oh sorry, I went off track there.

  @{i}Trinity  Player@{ui}  is  a  CD  player  that works with all SCSI/ATAPI CDROM
  drives and has quite a few features to mess about with.

  @{b}PLEASE   NOTE:@{ub}    @{i}Trinity  Player@{ui}   and  this  AmigaGuide  doc  file  is
  un-finished,  which  means  there's  sections  missing  and  things  not
  currently implemented.  Please watch out for updates (see @{"Author" link "5_Author"}) !
@EndNode

;################################################### REQUIREMENTS
@Node "1_Requirements" "Aha!  I'M Alan Partridge! .... er, no I'm not. Sorry."
  @{fg shine}@{u}                                                                        @{uu}@{fg text}

                 @{b}<·S·Y·S·T·E·M· ·R·E·Q·U·I·R·E·M·E·N·T·S·«@{ub}
  @{u}                                                                        @{uu}

  @{u}@{b}Hardware@{uu}@{ub}:
    Amiga with OS v2.04+
    SCSI/ATAPI CDROM drive
    Er... at least 1 audio CD!

  @{u}@{b}Software@{uu}@{ub}:
    Diskfont.library            - goes in LIBS:
    Mathtrans.library           - goes in LIBS:  (maybe required)
    Personal.font / 8           - goes in FONTS:
    XEN.font      / 8           - goes in FONTS:

  @{u}@{b}Other@{uu}@{ub}:
    You will need an Interlaced screenmode (e.g..  640x512) with the
    MagicWB (8 colours minimum) palette.

  You  @{u}CAN@{uu}  use @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} on a non-interlaced screen (with or
  without the MagicWB palette), but it'll look shite!
@EndNode

;################################################### FEATURES
@Node "1_Features" "I'm a Creature Feature! (TM)"
  @{fg shine}@{u}                                                                        @{uu}@{fg text}

                            @{b}«·F·E·A·T·U·R·E·S·»@{ub}
  @{u}                                                                        @{uu}

  ř @{fg shine}Looks great!@{fg text}
  ř Has standard CD player controls
    (Stop/Pause/Skip Back/Rewind/Play/Fast Forward/Skip Forward).
  ř @{fg shine}CDs can be ejected via the GUI.@{fg text}
  ř Extensive keyboard support (use the Function keys to play the
    corresponding tracks, use the Numeric Keypad, etc.).
  ř @{fg shine}Each CD can have it's own ID file (compatible with MCDPlayer,
    Skandalfo Player, MegaCD Player, etc.)  which is loaded when a
    valid Compact Disc is inserted. User specified path.@{fg text}
  ř A nice Track Editor which lets you edit the  current  CD's  ID
    file.  Tracks can also be played if the right mouse button is
    pressed while in the Track Editor. A CD ID can also be printed
    out or saved via the Track Editor.
  ř @{fg shine}CDs can be played/stopped/ejected on program start-up/exit.@{fg text}
  ř A Program Mode editor which lets  you  specify  which  tracks
    to play and in which order.
  ř @{fg shine}Preview Mode lets you play a user specified number of seconds
    of each track (sometimes called "Intro" in other CD players).@{fg text}
  ř Shuffle Mode which plays tracks in a random order.
  ř @{fg shine}Repeat Mode to repeat the current, er... mode.@{fg text}
  ř If you don't like the GUI graphics,  you can draw your own or
    use someone else's instead !!
  ř @{fg shine}Two GUI sizes.  The  big  one (ooer!)  for  people  with  big
    screens  and  the  minimised  version  for  people with small
    screens (for people that need every inch of available space).@{fg text}
  ř @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} can be opened on any (public) screen,  or  can
    be told to open it's own 8-colour Interlaced MagicWB screen.
  ř @{fg shine}The main window can be moved around via the cursor  keys  and
    can be moved in 5 preset locations by using the keys 1-5.@{fg text}
  ř @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} checks for changes in the System Preferences.
    If there's been a change,  you'll  be  asked  if  you want to
    close-down the main window and then re-appear to reflect  the
    changes (if any).
  ř @{fg shine}Extensive ARexx port. There's so many commands, you can write
    your own interface for @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} via ARexx !!@{fg text}
  ř On-line AmigaGuide documentation (not context sensitive - yet).
  ř @{fg shine}Partly font-sensitive.@{fg text}
  ř Commodity.
  ř @{fg shine}Only Ł5 !@{fg text}

                         @{b}@{u}OTHER NON-PROGRAM FEATURES@{uu}@{ub}

  @{b}*@{ub} @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} will be supported for a long time to come.
    So you can expect lots of regular updates!
  @{b}*@{ub} Blitz Basic 2 source code @{u}may@{uu} soon be available for Ł10.
  @{b}*@{ub} There is a (small) @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} mailing list.
@EndNode

;################################################### DISTRIBUTION
@Node "1_Distribution" "READ THIS CAREFULLY - AND TAKE NOTICE"
  @{fg shine}@{u}                                                                        @{uu}@{fg text}

                        @{b}<·D·I·S·T·R·I·B·U·T·I·O·N·>@{ub}
  @{u}                                                                        @{uu}

  The  demo  version  of  @{i}Trinity  Player@{ui}  and all associated files may be
  freely  distributed free of charge.  You are @{b}NOT@{ub} permitted to distribute
  any  of  the  files  seperately,  or if they've been modified by a third
  party (ie. not me).

  The  registered version of @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} must @{b}NOT@{ub} be distributed, doing
  so  will  break the law and make you liable for prosecution.  Registered
  users may @{b}NOT@{ub} use @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} on any other machine but their own.

  @{b}Magazines:@{ub}   If  you  put @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} on your cover disk/CD, you @{u}MUST@{uu}
  notify me via email and send me the issue that @{i}TP@{ui} appears on (CD version
  preferred).

  If  you  would  like  to distribute something in the main @{i}Trinity Player@{ui}
  archive,  then  please  send  it to the author for inclusion in the main
  archive  (it's upto the author if it may or may not be added to the main
  archive)  -  @{b}DO NOT@{ub} add it to the archive yourself, if you do, you'll be
  breaking the above condition.

  @{b}Amiga  Format:@{ub}   Where  the  hell  is  me  free issue?  I saw TP on your
  coverdisc,  but did you send me an issue?  Did you even notify me?  Like
  bollocks  you  did.   Ya  see  your  mag?  I ain't buying it anymore, so
  there!
@EndNode

;################################################### REGISTRATION
;Oh go on!  Please register!!  You know you want to! *sob*

@Node "1_Registration" "C'mon mate - register!  bum lick... slurp.. licky lick...etc"
  @{fg shine}@{u}                                                                        @{uu}@{fg text}

                       @{b}!·R·E·G·I·S·T·R·A·T·I·O·N·!@{ub}
  @{u}                                                                        @{uu}

  For  a  nice  crispy  Ł5  note, you can have the latest, FULL version of
  @{i}Trinity Player@{ui}!  No restrictions or anything!  Huzzah!

  Under  law,  you  @{b}@{u}CANNOT@{uu}@{ub}  distribute  your registered version of @{i}Trinity@{ui}
  @{i}Player@{ui}, as it's a criminal offence, and you'll be prosecuted. And I'll personally
  rip your pubes off with the sharp pointy bits in my Amiga's tower case.

  Sorry about that, but it had to be said.

  Oh, wanna know what you get?  Well, have a looky here:

   @{b}*@{ub} CD ID's loading/saving is enabled.  Just insert a CD and then it's ID
     file will automatically be loaded and displayed, so you get a list of
     all the tracks on the CD, etc.

   @{b}*@{ub} A track can be played by right-mouse clicking on  the  track  in  the
     Track Editor.

   @{b}*@{ub} Your   suggestions/ideas   will   have   a   higher   priority   than
     non-registered users,  so  will  be  acted upon  as soon as possible.
     Unless of course your suggestions/ideas is a tad un-feasible!  :)

   @{b}*@{ub} I  will  do  my  best  to  help  you  with any problems you're having
     regarding @{i}Trinity Player@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub} By  registering  you'll give me a greater incentive to do more on TP.
     I know all authors say this, but it's very true.

   @{b}*@{ub} You'll get your own @{u}personalised@{uu} copy of @{i}Trinity Player@{ui}!


                              @{b}@{u}VIA NORMAL POST@{uu}@{ub}
  To  register, send a Ł5 note (sorry, but @{u}only@{uu} Pounds Sterling accepted!)
  in  an envelope (stick it in-between a couple of bits of paper) together
  with the enclosed registration form on a disk to:

                              Joseph Cox
                              115 Corporation Road
                              Grimsby
                              N.E. Lincs
                              DN31 1UR
                              England


                                 @{b}@{u}VIA EMAIL@{uu}@{ub}
  You  can  alternatively  have  your registered version of @{i}Trinity Player@{ui}
  emailed  direct  to you within an hour of me getting your order.  Please
  notify  me  by email prior to sending me your registration.  Also attach
  the order form with your email.  @{i}Thanks!@{ui}

  If you're an already registered user and would like updates, either send
  me  a  disk + postage and I'll send you the latest version OR send me an
  email  requesting the latest version.  The latest non-registered version
  of @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} is available on my @{"website" link "5_Author"}.
@EndNode

