@Node "BIGWIN_20+" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} QSP - 20+

  As you can tell, the @{"QSP" link "QSP"} can only play the first 20 tracks.  This button
  is used to play any track over 20.

  When  you select it, a window will open asking you which track number to
  play.  *Enter it and then press Return.


  *You  must  first  clear the contents of the string gadget, as there's a
  zero in there.  Sorry, I can't do anything about it.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_PREFS" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Preferences

  Here  you  can  set  what CD device should be used for accessing your CD
  drive (default is squirrelscsi.device), unit ID, plus how TP runs, etc.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_TRACKTIME" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Track Time

  When  playing  a  CD, the Track Time will be updated to display how much
  time has elapsed since the start of the current playing track.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_REMAINING" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Remaining

  This  is  the  remaining  time for the currently playing track.  When it
  reaches 00:00, it's the end of the current track.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_TOTALDISC" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Total Disc

  This is the total combined track times' all the tracks on the current CD
  take up.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_CLOCK" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Clock

  This is the system time.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_REPEAT" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Repeat Mode

  When  this  is  enabled  (it'll  appear "lit"), it'll repeat the current
  mode.   For  example,  say you had @{"Shuffle" link "BIGWIN_SHUFFLE"} mode on, it'll keep radomally
  playing  different tracks when the current one finishes, instead of just
  playing one random track.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_SHUFFLE" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Shuffle Mode

  When  this  is enabled (it'll appear "lit") and you press @{"Play" link "BIGWIN_PLAY"}, a random
  track  will  be  played.   Enable  @{"Repeat" link "BIGWIN_REPEAT"} mode to keep on playing random
  tracks when the current one finishes.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_PREVIEW" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Preview Mode

  If you select @{"Play" link "BIGWIN_PLAY"} when this is enabled, a window will appear containing
  stats  and  will  start playing the intro of every track on the CD.  The
  time  each  track  plays  for  is  configurable in the @{"preferences" link "3_PrefsWindow"} under
  Preview Delay.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_PROGRAM" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Program Mode (@{i}not currently implemented@{ui})

  You  can  play a pre-selected (selected with the @{"Program Editor" link "3_ProgEdWindow"}) list of
  tracks using Program Mode.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_EJECT" "Usage / Big Window (BigGUI mode)"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Eject

  This  will  eject  the currently inserted CD.  If in @{"Play" link "BIGWIN_PLAY"}/@{"Pause" link "BIGWIN_PAUSE"} mode and
  you  select this, a requester will appear informing you of that fact and
  will  ask you if you either want to Stop and Eject the CD, just Stop the
  CD or Cancel the Eject request.

  @{b}NOTE:@{ub}  Eject only works on CD drive with a motorised tray.  Seeing as my
  CD  drive  hasn't got a motorised tray, I can't experiment with Eject to
  try and get it to retract the CD tray.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_STOP" "Usage / Main Controls"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Stop

  This will stop a currently playing CD.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_PLAY" "Usage / Main Controls"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Play

  This  will  start  the  current CD playing.  You can use the @{"QSP" link "QSP"} to play
  specific tracks without needing to repeatedly click on @{"Next Track" link "BIGWIN_NEXTTRACK"}.

  Clicking  on  Play  while  in  @{"Pause" link "BIGWIN_PAUSE"} mode will start play from the first
  track.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_PAUSE" "Usage / Main Controls"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Pause

  This  will  pause a currently playing CD.  You can have the pause button
  flash  when  the  CD  is  paused,  if  you  want  -  have  a look at the
  @{"PAUSE_FLASH" link "PREFS_PAUSE_FLASH"} tooltype.

  Click again to un-pause the CD.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_PREVTRACK" "Usage / Main Controls"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Previous Track

  When  in  @{"Play" link "BIGWIN_PLAY"}  mode, clicking Previous Track will go back one track and
  continue playing from there.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_REWIND" "Usage / Main Controls"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Rewind

  Clicking  on  Rewind  while playing a track will rewind the track by the
  amount of seconds specified in the @{"preferences" link "3_PrefsWindow"}.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_FASTFORWARD" "Usage / Main Controls"

  @{b}@{u}BigGUI@{uu} -@{ub} Fast Forward

  This  is the opposite of @{"Rewind" link "BIGWIN_REWIND"} - it'll fast forward through the current
  track by the amount of seconds specified in the @{"preferences" link "3_PrefsWindow"}.
@EndNode

@Node "BIGWIN_NEXTTRACK" "Usage / Main Controls"

  @{b}@{u}BigWin@{uu} -@{ub} Next Track

  Just  like  @{"Previous  Track" link "BIGWIN_PREVTRACK"}, this will go to the next track.  The screen
  will flash if you try advancing past the last track.
@EndNode


