  @{u}                                                                           @{uu}
  @{fg shine}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{fg text}
  @{b}@{u}V0.70  -  7th April, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}!@{ub}@{fg text}Clicking on PAL/NTSC in the preferences will now actually set the UPDATE
  RATE for you instead of informing you of the value (I didn't know how to
  set it myself before).

 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}When  selecting  a track using the @{"QSP" link "QSP"}, it won't keep trying to play the
  first  second  of  the 1st track repeatedly and toggling track #1 on the
  @{"QSP" link "QSP"}.


  @{b}@{u}V0.71  -  6th May, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Started  and  completed  the  @{"TP_Installer" link "2_Install_Auto"}  program which automatically
  installs @{i}TP@{ui}, plus the demo CD ID files (if requested).

 @{fg shine}@{b}!@{ub}@{fg text}Wrote more of this .guide file.


  @{b}@{u}V0.71  -  17th May, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Added @{i}TP@{ui}'s @{"GUI GFX" link "2_Install_GFX"} to the archive.

 @{fg shine}@{b}!@{ub}@{fg text}Wrote  more  of  this  .guide file.  Also  made it look better by adding
  "3D" lines, etc.


  @{b}@{u}V0.72  -  07th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Added @{"Tooltypes" link "3_ToolTypes"}.


  @{b}@{u}V0.73  -  10th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}Sorted out  the problem of the @{"Preferences Window" link "3_PrefsWindow"} locking the system up
  when  opened.   Turns  out  that  this would happen if the Personal font
  wasn't  installed.   @{i}TP@{ui}  now  opens  the Topaz font is the Personal font
  couldn't be found. Added the Personal font to the @{i}TP@{ui} archive.
  Major thanks to @{i}Liz Tucker@{ui}.

 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}When @{i}TP@{ui} couldn't open the @{"Song Editor" link "3_SongEdWindow"} window, @{i}TP@{ui} went into an infinite
  loop trying to open it, due to a STUPID typo by me.

 @{fg shine}@{b}!@{ub}@{fg text}As  far  as  I'm  aware,  right clicking a highlighted track in the Song
  Editor window works perfectly now.

 @{fg shine}@{b}!@{ub}@{fg text}Changed  the "TerraForm" badge to "Carnage" in the main window..  should
  have done this ages ago...

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Updated the @{"Installer" link "2_Install_Auto"} to automatically install the Personal fonts if not
  found.

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Added 3 more DiscID's (@{i}Off Yer Nut!!@{ui}).

 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}When selecting  PAL/NTSC  in the @{"Preferences window" link "3_PrefsWindow"}, @{i}TP@{ui} would instantly
  forgot  it  and  revert  back  to  the  value  just  before PAL/NTSC was
  selected.
  Thanks to @{i}Robert Johnston@{ui}.

 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}The TITLE and GROUP fields in the CD ID files were being loaded/saved in
  the wrong order.
  Thanks to @{i}Robert Johnston@{ui}.

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}The  "xx:  " (first 4 characters) is stripped from the @{"SONG_NAME" link "AREXX_INFO_CD" 17} (ARexx)
  command.
  Requested by @{i}Robert Johnston@{ui}.

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Added @{"OPEN_OWN_SCREEN" link "PREFS_OPEN_OWN_SCREEN"}, @{"WINDOW_BORDER" link "PREFS_WINDOW_BORDER"} and @{"AUTO_ACTIVATE" link "PREFS_AUTO_ACTIVATE"} tooltypes.


  @{b}@{u}V0.73  -  11th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}When  there  is no CD in the drive, then user is not allowed to go in to
  the @{"Song  Editor" link "3_SongEdWindow"}  -  this  stops  a very potential crash happening when
  there's no tracks available.


  @{b}@{u}V0.73  -  13th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}Numerous small bug fixes which hopefully makes @{i}TP@{ui} more stable.


  @{b}@{u}V0.73  -  14th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{i}TP@{ui} crashed when clicking on either Rewind, Fast Forward or Eject (forgot
  to check to see if there was a CD inserted/playing first).

  @{b}@{u}V0.74  -  14th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}@{i}TP@{ui}'s  commodity  hotkey  is  now  set  to  whatever  is specified in the
  @{"Tooltypes" link "3_Tooltypes"} (sorry, I forgot!).


  @{b}@{u}V0.74  -  15th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Added the XEN font to the archive (required by TP).


  @{b}@{u}V0.74  -  17th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}!@{ub}@{fg text}Started work on the new Preferences menu/windows.

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Added @{"EXTERNAL_GFX" link "PREFS_EXTERNAL_GFX"} tooltype.


  @{b}@{u}V0.74  -  18th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}When playing track >21, other buttons appeared de-pressed instead of "21+".
  Thanks to @{i}Robert Johnston@{ui}.

 @{fg shine}@{b}!@{ub}@{fg text}Made the "Preview" window font sensitive (sorry).

 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}A  "Fatal Error" message (beware:  always dread these!) came up when the
  CD finished playing while in @{"SmallGUI" link "3_SmallWindow"} mode.

 @{fg shine}@{b}!@{ub}@{fg text}Stopped  all  flickering  that sometimes happens when updating the Track
  times.  If not, I've certainly reduced it.  The reason was that I wasn't
  drawing  (well,  BLITting)  the  times'  in sync with the video-beam.  I
  didn't want to waste any time..  but it works perfectly now anyway.

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}While  in  the @{"Song Editor" link "3_SongEdWindow"}, it is possible to send the current CD's data
  to a file or printer.

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Pressing  HELP  on  the  keyboard will bring up this .guide file if it's
  found.  Sorry, I forgot to add this "feature".

 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}For  some  reason the @{"QSP" link "QSP"} wasn't updated when the current track finished
  and moved on to the next one.


  @{b}@{u}V0.74  -  19th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Spent all afternoon getting the External GUI GFX routine working.  Turns
  out  that  I  basically had the routine working within 20 minutes, but a
  variable type error (I used a .f float type instead of a .l long type by
  accident) caused me to waste LOTS of time.  Sh*t.


  @{b}@{u}V0.75  -  22th June, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}Even  if a CD wasn't in play/pause mode, TP would still bring up the "CD
  is   in   play/pause   mode"  requester.   This  error  was  due  to  me
  "spring-cleaning" this section of the code.
  Reported by @{i}Robert Johnston@{ui}.

 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}Sorted  out  all the probs regarding SmallGUI mode (titles not updating,
  etc).
  Pointed out by @{i}Robert Johnston@{ui}.

 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}When  a CD is in the drive that doesn't have a corresponding CD ID file,
  @{i}TP@{ui} will now display "Unknown CD" instead of displaying nothing.
  Suggested by @{i}Robert Johnston@{ui}.

 @{fg shine}@{b}!@{ub}@{fg text}Finally  got CD recognition working!  No more having to go into SmallGUI
  mode and then back into BigGUI mode for TP to read in the new CD!  Phew!

 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}The  return  values  for  @{"WINDOW_TYPE" link "AREXX_INFO_Window"}  (ARexx)  was the @{b}wrong way round@{ub}.
  Corrected.   Also,  @{"SCREEN_MODE" link "AREXX_INFO_Screen" 35} was shown as SCREEN_DISPLAY in the @{"ARexx" link "3_ARexx"}
  section.  Also corrected.


  @{b}@{u}V0.80  -  14th October, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}.@{ub}@{fg text}Bloody hell! I haven't done anything for ages! I suppose
  I'd better start catching up, eh? :}

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Phew, I've almost completed the Program feature.
  So  now  you  can  create your own playlists and play tracks in whatever
  order  you  want.   It only plays the first track in the playlist though
  for some reason....


  @{b}@{u}V0.80  -  27th October, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}*@{ub}@{fg text}Added a check to see if the host system has got exec version 39 or above, as the
  online help for the Prefs/Program Mode editor's needs v39 or above.

 @{fg shine}@{b}!@{ub}@{fg text}MAJOR  optimisations  in  the  keyboard  reading routine.  Instead of 42
  seperate key checks, there's only 1. Hmm.


  @{b}@{u}V0.80  -  21st November, 1998.@{uu}@{ub}
 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Re-structured  the  @{"About" link "3_AboutWindow"}  menu and added an extensive "Statistics" menu
  containing  usefile  and  non-useful  info  for  you  to have a look at.
  Haven't added this info to the doc (this thing yer reading) yet though.
  Still some more to add to the Statistics bit, by the way.

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Ya  see  that  "CDROM  suite"  thing  in  the @{"Future" link "4_Future"} section?  I've been
  incorporating  it  into  the @{i}TP@{ui} archive, and soon @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} will be
  released  as  @{i}The  Trinity  Suite@{ui}  as there'll be more than just @{i}Trinity@{ui}
  @{i}Player@{ui} - they'll be a CD audio ripper.... just have a look at the @{"Futore" link "4_Future"}
  section.

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Added another GUI mode (TinyGUI).  SmallGUI is still pretty big, so I've
  added  this  new mode.  Mad people using TP in a non-interlaced mode can
  now  at  least  use it without it taking up a stupid amount of space.  I
  didn't  make TinyGUI any smaller as it would be far too small for people
  that are using TP in interlaced (but they'd be using TP in BigGUI mode..
  .. yadda yadda).

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Added @{"ShowTips" link "3_Tooltypes"}. Shows you tips upon program startup.

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Various things added/optimised.


  @{b}@{u}V0.80  -  xxnd January, 1999.@{uu}@{ub}

 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}
 @{fg shine}@{b}+@{ub}@{fg text}Right mouse button brings up a menu instead of switching GUI modes.

@EndNode

;################################################### FUTURE
;
@Node "4_Future" "Here for the future"
  @{fg shine}@{u}                                                                        @{uu}@{fg text}

                               @{b}·F·U·T·U·R·E·@{ub}
  @{u}                                                                        @{uu}

  Create  some  sort  of  "CDROM  suite",  which  will  have  a  main menu
  (GadTools,  MagicWB  and  MUI versions) from which you can select to run
  the  CD  player  (Trinity  Player),  the  CD  audio  ripper (save (parts
  of/full)  tracks  on  to  your  HD  in IFF, RAW, etc formats - currently
  hasn't  got  a  name  yet)  and  maybe  a  CD Info (gives details on the
  currently inserted CD and the CD drive) program.

  Completely  new  preferences  module,  which will be a seperate program.
  Which  will  make  the  main TP exe smaller and hopefully faster.  There
  will be GadTools, MagicWB and @{b}possibly@{ub} a MUI version  - but  I  wouldn't
  count on it.

  Add a catalogue/locale system.

  More @{"ARexx" link "3_ARexx"} commands (anyone?).

  Stamp out every single gonadding bug!
@EndNode

